article.headline: UC Santa Barbara has won 10 of past 11 games
article.linkText: Gauchos pull away from UC Irvine with key run
article.story:
IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Lindsay Taylor scored 20 points and grabbed nine rebounds and No. 19 UC Santa Barbara went on a 24-3 run midway through the second half to defeat UC Irvine 78-56 Saturday night.

	   Mia Fisher added 14 points and Brandy Richardson had 13 points
and nine rebounds for the Gauchos (21-4, 13-1 Big West Conference),
who have won three in a row and 10 of their last 11.

	   Christina Callaway had 19 points and eight rebounds while Wendy
Gabbe scored 13 for the Anteaters (16-10, 9-6).

	   The game was tied at 44 with 12:47 to play, but Lisa Willett
made a 3-pointer and Fisher hit a 10-foot jumper to give UC Santa
Barbara a 49-44 lead with 11:36 remaining.

	   Taylor scored 10 points during the decisive run that extended
the Gauchos' lead to 75-51 with 2:03 left.

	   The Anteaters failed to score for a stretch of 5:32 in the
second half.

	   Santa Barbara shot 54.5 percent in the second half and
outrebounded Irvine 50-28 for the game.
